<inglise> Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1963/79 of 6 September 1979 laying down detailed rules for the application of the production refund on olive oil used in the manufacture of certain preserved foods </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1963/79, milles s&auml;testatakse teatavate konservide tootmisel kasutatava oliivi&otilde;li tootmistoetuse &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad 6. september 1979 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organization of the market in oils and fats (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 590/79 (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 22. septembri 1966. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust nr 136/66/EM&Uuml; &otilde;li- ja rasvaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kehtestamise kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 590/79, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2749/78 of 23 November 1978 on trade in oils and fats between the Community and Greece (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1978. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2749/78 &otilde;li- ja rasvakaubanduse kohta &uuml;henduse ja Kreeka vahel, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 591/79 of 26 March 1979 laying down general rules concerning the production refund for olive oils used in the manufacture of certain preserved foods (4), and in particular Article 9 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 26. m&auml;rtsi 1979. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 591/79, millega n&auml;hakse ette teatavate konservide tootmisel kasutatava oliivi&otilde;li tootmistoetuse &uuml;ldeeskirjad, eriti selle artiklit 9, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the control arrangements provided for in Article 8 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 591/79 must ensure that the production refund is granted only in respect of olive oil which satisfies the conditions laid down in the present Regulation and in Regulation (EEC) No 591/79; whereas, in principle, the refund should be granted only after that control has been effected; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 591/79 artikli 8 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud kontrollikord peab tagama, et tootmistoetust antakse &uuml;ksnes oliivi&otilde;li puhul, mis vastab k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses ning m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 591/79 s&auml;testatud tingimustele; p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt tuleks tootmistoetust anda alles p&auml;rast k&otilde;nealust kontrolli; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, if the control is to be properly effected, the application to have it effected should be submitted in good time and should contain certain basic information; whereas, to that same end, manufacturers of fish and vegetable preserves should be required to keep stock accounts indicating the quantity and origin of the olive oil used; </inglise>
<eesti> kontrolli n&otilde;uetekohaseks teostamiseks tuleks kontrollitaotlus esitada &otilde;igeaegselt ning see peaks sisaldama teatavat p&otilde;hiteavet; samal eesm&auml;rgil tuleks kala- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljakonservide tootjatelt n&otilde;uda laoarvestuse pidamist kasutatud oliivi&otilde;li koguse ja p&auml;ritolu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the control must extend over a period which will allow processors to plan their production in the light of cost prices and to obtain supplies of olive oil; whereas, for the same reasons, the refund to be granted should be the refund valid on the day on which the application to have the control effected is submitted; </inglise>
<eesti> kontroll peab toimuma ajavahemiku jooksul, mis lubaks t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatel omahinda silmas pidades toodangut planeerida ning oliivi&otilde;li hankida; samadel p&otilde;hjustel peaks antav tootmistoetus olema toetus, mis kehtib kontrollitaotluse esitamise p&auml;eval; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, to enable the parties concerned to buy the olive oil they require, Member States should be free to pay the amount of the refund in advance, subject to the provision of a security; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks, et v&otilde;imaldada asjaomastel pooltel osta vajaminevat oliivi&otilde;li, peaks liikmesriikidel olema v&otilde;imalik maksta toetussumma ette, juhul kui on esitatud tagatis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 615/71 (5) should be repealed; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 615/71 tuleks tunnistada kehtetuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Oils and Fats, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las &otilde;li- ja rasvaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For purposes of the production refund, manufacturers of the fish and vegetable preserved foods referred to in Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 591/79 shall keep, in respect of the said preserved foods, daily stock accounts giving at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmistoetuse saamiseks peavad m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 591/79 artiklis 2 osutatud kala- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljakonservide tootjad nimetatud konservide kohta igap&auml;evast laoarvestust, m&auml;rkides v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmise teabe: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the quantity of olive oil, broken down by origin and date of entry into the factory; </inglise>
<eesti> a) oliivi&otilde;li kogus p&auml;ritolu ja vabrikusse saabumise kuup&auml;eva j&auml;rgi; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the quantity of olive oil, broken down by origin, used in the manufacture of the preserved food; </inglise>
<eesti> b) konservide tootmisel kasutatud oliivi&otilde;li kogus p&auml;ritolu j&auml;rgi; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) in respect of each incoming batch of olive oil, the number of the invoice, receipt or any other equivalent document; </inglise>
<eesti> c) arve, kviitungi v&otilde;i muu samav&auml;&auml;rse dokumendi number iga saabuva oliivi&otilde;lipartii kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the net weight of preserved food produced, with indication of the average weight of olive oil employed for each type of manufacture. </inglise>
<eesti> d) toodetud konservide netomass; m&auml;rkida iga t&uuml;&uuml;pi tootmise juures kasutatud oliivi&otilde;li keskmine mass. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to qualify for the production refund, the manufacturer must submit a request for verification to the competent authority not later than five working days before the date envisaged for the commencement of manufacturing operations. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmistoetuse saamiseks peab tootja esitama kontrollitaotluse p&auml;devale asutusele hiljemalt 5 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva enne tootmistegevuse kavandatud alguskuup&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise> Such an application may not be submitted to the competent authority until the oil is in the manufacturing premises. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda taotlust ei v&otilde;i p&auml;devale asutusele esitada enne, kui &otilde;li on tootmisettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The application must contain at least the following information: </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlus peab sisaldama v&auml;hemalt j&auml;rgmist teavet: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the name and address of the manufacturer; </inglise>
<eesti> a) tootja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the dates on which manufacture is to begin and end; </inglise>
<eesti> b) tootmise algus- ja l&otilde;ppkuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the quantity and type of preserved food to be manufactured; </inglise>
<eesti> c) toodetavate konservide kogus ja liik; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the quantity of olive oil expected to be used in the manufacture, and the origin of the oil. </inglise>
<eesti> d) tootmises kasutatava oliivi&otilde;li eeldatav kogus ning &otilde;li p&auml;ritolu. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The request for verification shall be valid only for a manufacturing process to be completed within a period ending not later than the last day of the third month following that in which the application was submitted. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollitaotlus kehtib &uuml;ksnes sellise tootmisprotsessi suhtes, mis l&otilde;petatakse hiljemalt taotluse esitamise kuule j&auml;rgneva kolmanda kuu viimasel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> If by reason of force majeure manufacture cannot be carried out within this period the competent agency of the Member State concerned shall, on request by the manufacturer, extend the period to the extent considered necessary having regard to the circumstances invoked. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&otilde;nealuse ajavahemiku jooksul ei ole tootmine v&otilde;imalik v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u t&otilde;ttu, pikendab asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus tootja taotlusel ajavahemikku vajalikul m&auml;&auml;ral, v&otilde;ttes arvesse tekkinud asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall check: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kontrollivad, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) that the manufacturer's stock record is kept in accordance with Article 1; </inglise>
<eesti> a) tootja peab laoarvestust vastavalt artiklile 1; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) that the oil indicated in the request for verification was on the premises at the time the application was submitted. </inglise>
<eesti> b) kontrollitaotluses m&auml;rgitud oliivi&otilde;li oli laos taotluse esitamise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The production refund shall be granted on application by the manufacturer within the Member State where the preserved food was manufactured. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmistoetus makstakse tootja taotluse alusel selles liikmesriigis, kus konservid toodeti. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The application referred to in paragraph 1 must include details of the quantity of oil employed in manufacturing the preserved food and its origin. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud taotlus peab sisaldama &uuml;ksikasjalikke andmeid konservide tootmisel kasutatud &otilde;li koguse ja p&auml;ritolu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The application must be submitted by the party concerned within six months from the date when the oil was used. </inglise>
<eesti> Taotluse peab asjaomane pool esitama kuue kuu jooksul alates &otilde;li kasutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The refund shall be paid when the Member State concerned has verified that the quantity of oil shown in the application referred to in Article 4 and the quantity and origin of oil employed in manufacturing the preserved food correspond. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetus makstakse p&auml;rast seda, kui asjaomane liikmesriik on kontrollinud artiklis 4 osutatud taotluses m&auml;rgitud &otilde;likoguse vastavust konservide tootmisel kasutatud &otilde;likogusele. </eesti>
<inglise> However, at the request of the party concerned, the refund may be paid in advance as soon as the check referred to in Article 3 has been carried out, on condition that a security is provided to guarantee that the oil will be used for the purposes specified. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomase poole taotlusel v&otilde;ib toetuse siiski maksta ette kohe p&auml;rast artiklis 3 osutatud kontrolli tingimusel, et on esitatud tagatis, et &otilde;li kasutatakse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud otstarbel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of the verification referred to in the first paragraph of Article 5, the Member State shall inter alia check the stock accounts referred to in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 5 esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud kontrolli eesm&auml;rgil kontrollivad liikmesriigid muuhulgas ka artiklis 1 osutatud laoarvestust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> If the quantity of olive oil mentioned in the application referred to in Article 4 and the quantity of oil used as shown by the verification referred to in Article 5 do not correspond, the Member State concerned shall assess the quantity of olive oil in respect of which the refund is payable. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artiklis 4 osutatud taotluses m&auml;rgitud oliivi&otilde;likogus ei vasta artiklis 5 osutatud kontrollis ilmnenud &otilde;likogusele, otsustab asjaomane liikmesriik, kui suurele oliivi&otilde;likogusele makstakse toetust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> The refund granted shall be that valid on the day on which the request for verification referred to in Article 2 was submitted. </inglise>
<eesti> Antav toetus on toetus, mis kehtib artiklis 2 osutatud kontrollitaotluse esitamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> The amount referred to in Article 4 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 591/79 shall be 0 750 ECU. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 591/79 artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud summa on 0,50 ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> However, where the arithmetic mean referred to in the first subparagraph of Article 4 (1) of the abovementioned Regulation is zero, the refund shall be fixed at zero. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 1 esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud aritmeetiline keskmine on null, on toetuse m&auml;&auml;r null. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 615/71 is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga tunnistatakse m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 615/71 kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 10 September 1979. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 10. septembril 1979. aastal. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply to olive oil in respect of which the requests referred to in Article 2 are submitted on or after that date. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse oliivi&otilde;li suhtes, mille kohta esitati artiklis 2 osutatud taotlus k&otilde;nealusel kuup&auml;eval v&otilde;i p&auml;rast seda. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards oil in respect of which the requests referred to in Article 2 are submitted prior to that date, Regulation (EEC) No 615/71 shall continue to apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Oliivi&otilde;li suhtes, mille kohta esitati taotlus enne k&otilde;nealust kuup&auml;eva, kohaldatakse j&auml;tkuvalt m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 615/71. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 6 September 1979. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 6. september 1979 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Finn GUNDELACH Vice-President </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel asepresident Finn GUNDELACH </eesti>
 